Manage Authorizations

You can manage your own moderator groups, by creating custom tokens that users can use to log into your account with reduced access. These tokens can be used instead of your normal login password, and will allow users to create update and remove items on your behalf. You can revoke access at anytime

This button open and closes access to iSearch Kelowna's advanced search. When it is open you will see a number of different filters on the left hand side that will allow you to quickly view individual, and combined, filters.

When the bar is open, try clicking on several of the filter icons and see how the map changes.
Use the search bar to see a list of markers of housing service providers, agencies and drop-in services. Click on the “reset filter” button on the left of the search bar to clear the filters.
